Question: Do you have any additional ideas, concerns, or feedback you would like to share to help ACME better serve the public?

Response ID: resp_2118
Response Text: I think my feedback would be to maintain the level of fairness for grants that was there this year. 
I realize this is possibly swayed because we received the Elevate grant for this year, but the requirements were frankly quite simple and if an organization is legitimately concerned with amplifying underrepresented communities, it was a pretty easy process. All the materials (last year's reviews on youtube, meetings with grant reviewers, a very clear rubric) were available to everyone and in my opinion, the backlash on who did(n't) receive Elevate funding this year was mostly unfounded. Organizations relied on years of receiving the grant as an expected funding source instead of something they should be consistently working towards. They turned on small organizations like ours who received grants and made us feel like we were undeserving when in reality, they didn't complete the application properly. It has been frustrating to say the least, but overall we are so grateful to the grant program for being so clear in its expectations and hope that level of clarity, fairness, and objective review is maintained through these shifts.

